The paper proposes a new recurrent network architecture that improves upon existing models, making it likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories. The experiments conducted involve human activity recognition and language modeling, which are both natural language processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting a possible classification under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of the proposed network for regression on synthetic data and image recognition tasks may also place it under computer vision (cs.CV).
